description:
In this episode of ANN Profiles, Alyssa Truman interviews Marcos Bomfim, the director of the Stewardship Department of the Seventh-day Adventist Church. Bomfim shares his Adventist journey, from struggling with low self-esteem to rediscovering his faith through family worship. He emphasizes the importance of parents making it a law for their children to attend church, as it can increase the likelihood of them developing a relationship with God. 

This episode highlights the significance of family and community in developing and sustaining one's faith. Watch now to learn more about Marcos Bomfim’s Adventist journey.

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.
